      <section eId="sec_44_14_238">
        <num>44-14-238</num>
        <content>
          <p>If a mortgage on personalty is given to secure several debts falling due at different times, the mortgagee may foreclose when the first debt becomes due; and the court will control the surplus so as to protect the lien created for the debts not due.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 1967; Code 1868, § 1955; Code 1873, § 1965; Code 1882, § 1965; Civil Code 1895, § 2739; Civil Code 1910, § 3272; Code 1933, § 67-1001.)</p>
        </content>
